1
00:00:01,090 --> 00:00:12,220
♪

2
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:15,010
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:15,010 --> 00:01:33,100
♪

4
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:38,230
(fighting and groaning)

5
00:01:38,230 --> 00:01:46,060
♪

6
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:48,090
Okay, I-I got it,

7
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:50,200
we got it,
we made a big mistake.

8
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,280
We shouldn't fight you,

9
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:54,140
you're just too
strong to handle.

10
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:55,250
Fine, I'm done.

11
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:57,190
I'm glad you figured things out.

12
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:59,030
What?

13
00:01:59,030 --> 00:02:02,000
Somehow I thought
you four could test me.

14
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,050
(chuckles)

15
00:02:03,050 --> 00:02:05,110
I guess I should've
known better.

16
00:02:05,110 --> 00:02:08,280
♪

17
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:11,280
Where must I go to find
an opponent worth fighting?

18
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:17,270
♪

19
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:21,010
Not last night but
the night before...

20
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:22,110
(laughing)

21
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,250
...thirty-two ninjas
came knocking at my door.

22
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:26,100
Kori's a pretty good juggler.

23
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,000
Good juggler, Kori.

24
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,130
...I hit them
with a rolling pin.

25
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:32,210
Yeah, even ugly girl's
good for something else

26
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:33,270
besides kendo.

27
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:35,110
Hmm--ow!

28
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:37,010
Hey, Kori, what'd
you do that for?

29
00:02:37,010 --> 00:02:39,010
I was just trying to
pay you a compliment!

30
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:40,200
I've got some news
for you, Yoshi.

31
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,010
With that kind of attitude,

32
00:02:42,010 --> 00:02:43,260
girls will never want
to be around you.

33
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:45,040
Well, the way you act,

34
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,020
no guy would ever want to
get near you, raccoon face.

35
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:49,030
I've had it!

36
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,050
(blowing raspberry)

37
00:02:50,050 --> 00:02:51,180
Come back here, you!

38
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:54,210
Well, I guess I'd better
start making lunch.

39
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:57,150
Kenshin, so what's on
your menu for lunch today?

40
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:59,000
Hmm...

41
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,100
Kohlrabi and duck foot soup.

42
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,150
Hey, wait!

43
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,060
I can also bring out my eggplant

44
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:06,120
that I've been pickling
underground for us.

45
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,050
I really hate eggplant.

46
00:03:08,050 --> 00:03:10,270
I wish we had some money so
we could all go out to eat.

47
00:03:10,270 --> 00:03:13,260
Because of our vegetable garden,
we always have a lot to eat,

48
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:15,220
but until we get
more dojo students,

49
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:17,280
we don't have enough money
to eat at a restaurant.

50
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:20,150
Boy, would it be great if
we had some paying students,

51
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:23,090
but the only thing we're
collecting at this dojo is dust.

52
00:03:23,090 --> 00:03:24,240
Hey, outta my way!

53
00:03:26,130 --> 00:03:28,140
(door creaking open)

54
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:31,210
There's some money in here!

55
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:34,050
Oh, brother, that
Kori's at it again!

56
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,130
Oh, no.

57
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,250
(laughing)

58
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:50,010
Oh, man, her brain got
warped by all that dust.

59
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:51,160
(laughing)

60
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,280
Here it is!

61
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,140
My great uncle left this to me.

62
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:56,230
Just what is it?

63
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:58,130
Don't you know about art?

64
00:03:58,130 --> 00:04:00,140
It's a painting!

65
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:03,190
My, those certainly are
skilled brush strokes.

66
00:04:03,190 --> 00:04:05,180
Is it an original
painting, Kori?

67
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:07,000
My great uncle painted it.

68
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,160
He was a skilled martial artist

69
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,030
and also a very
talented ink painter.

70
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:13,050
This should bring us
some good money.

71
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:14,090
Thank you.

72
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:16,090
Great Uncle Shinto
always wanted his art

73
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:18,150
to bring people happiness,
and by selling it,

74
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:20,240
we will all happily
enjoy a great meal!

75
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,010
Huh?

76
00:04:23,010 --> 00:04:24,270
Yes, that's the way to go, Kori.

77
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:27,110
Thanks for saving me
from that pickled eggplant!

78
00:04:27,110 --> 00:04:28,110
(laughing)

79
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:30,120
What a nice attitude adjustment.

80
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,270
Yay, hot beef pot!

81
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:34,210
(chuckling)

82
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:42,070
Your lunch is served.

83
00:04:44,130 --> 00:04:46,150
Yoshi, don't just
gulp your food down,

84
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:48,280
it's unhealthy,
and you'll choke.

85
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,210
(chewing rapidly)

86
00:04:50,210 --> 00:04:52,130
I tried to warn you, Yoshi.

87
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:54,250
Come on, spit it out,
and you're gonna be just fine.

88
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:57,210
Instead of beef pot,
order soup next time, Yoshi.

89
00:04:57,210 --> 00:04:59,120
Just shut up and listen.

90
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,060
♪

91
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:04,000
Democracy will never be
reached by peaceful methods.

92
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,160
Violence is the only way.

93
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,040
Are you saying the
only way to change

94
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:09,020
is to assassinate
leaders of our government?

95
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:11,050
We should try to change
things peacefully first,

96
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,100
then if that doesn't work,

97
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,130
maybe we should
try violent means.

98
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:15,210
Change your thinking.

99
00:05:15,210 --> 00:05:17,280
If it takes acts
of treason, then so be it.

100
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,140
If you keep up
that kind of talk,

101
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:21,020
then someone's sure
to report you.

102
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,190
Well, I'm not afraid
to crack a few heads.

103
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:25,030
♪

104
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:26,220
I believe in democracy, too,

105
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:28,200
but those guys are
just too extreme.

106
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:31,060
What do you mean, too extreme?

107
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:33,170
Unfortunately,
some men think violence

108
00:05:33,170 --> 00:05:35,090
is the only way
to change things.

109
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:38,190
If they were to try and stop me,
they'd be pushing up daisies.

110
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:40,090
Bottoms up.

111
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:42,120
Listen, let's order
another bottle of sake.

112
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,280
Democracy is a really good idea,

113
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,290
but these men are willing
to kill to get what they want.

114
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:51,100
Too bad our meal's being
ruined by a bunch of drunks.

115
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:54,290
Let's hope they all just
pass out in a little while.

116
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:56,030
-Hmm?
-Hmm?

117
00:05:58,290 --> 00:06:00,080
(screaming)

118
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:02,210
(gasps)

119
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:05,150
Kenshin!

120
00:06:05,150 --> 00:06:07,040
That was quite a blow.

121
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,120
Kenshin, are you okay?

122
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:12,090
♪

123
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:14,110
All right, let's go.

124
00:06:14,110 --> 00:06:16,200
That's just great, you start
throwing around dishes,

125
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,100
and because of you,
we have to leave.

126
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:21,020
Yeah, you clocked
him, you leave.

127
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:22,210
Excuse me for
interrupting, guys,

128
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:24,200
but I need to make
a request of you.

129
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,200
Which of you boneheads
was responsible

130
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,080
for hitting my
friend in the head?

131
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,110
What was that?

132
00:06:29,110 --> 00:06:31,040
If I were you, kid,
I'd keep my mouth shut

133
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,250
unless you want to be
spitting out teeth,

134
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:35,150
so you better just bug off
before you get hurt.

135
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:38,020
Hey, is that what
democracy's all about?

136
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:39,090
Apologize!

137
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:41,070
You better listen closely, kid.

138
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,240
What do you know about anything?

139
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,080
You're just some
smart-mouthed punk

140
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:46,110
who thinks I won't mop the
floor with ya because you're--

141
00:06:46,110 --> 00:06:48,030
Excuse me.

142
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:50,130
I'm going to have to
ask you to leave here.

143
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:51,120
Huh?

144
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,130
What's that?

145
00:06:52,130 --> 00:06:53,230
Get the hell outta here!

146
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:54,250
(gasping)

147
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,190
I've always thought democracy

148
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:01,090
was to help the
powerless people,

149
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:03,110
but I guess the democracy
you guys talk about

150
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:07,200
is the freedom to behave
like stupid drunks.

151
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,270
Based on what I just
saw you jerks do,

152
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:12,270
I'd have to say that now
you need to make two apologies.

153
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,060
We're not sorry for anything.

154
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,070
Are you all right, ma'am?

155
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:16,120
Uh-huh.

156
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:19,130
You better run unless you're
ready to rumble, skinny.

157
00:07:19,130 --> 00:07:24,000
Maybe you boys need to get
knocked down a few pegs.

158
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,080
(grumbling)

159
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,060
Usually in life,
we try to avoid a fight,

160
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:29,060
but you three seem
determined to start one,

161
00:07:29,060 --> 00:07:30,090
so I'll oblige you.

162
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:32,270
You see, I hate people
that pick on the powerless.

163
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:34,250
I can't stand
when guys like you

164
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,240
talk about
democracy and fairness

165
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:40,290
and then go around giving
those words a bad name.

166
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:43,140
So, boys, isn't it about time?

167
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:45,060
I'd say now is the time.

168
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:47,230
Okay, you've had it,
let's go outside.

169
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:54,130
♪

170
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:55,290
(laughing)

171
00:07:55,290 --> 00:07:59,280
♪

172
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,130
(laughing)

173
00:08:01,130 --> 00:08:04,010
♪

174
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:06,130
I'm not sure we
should let this happen.

175
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:08,190
You think I should jump
in and stop this fight?

176
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:10,230
Don't do it, he's the one
that wanted to challenge them,

177
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:12,000
so it's his fight.

178
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,250
All right, come on, it's time
to get down to business.

179
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:18,110
I don't plan on
battling you with my fists.

180
00:08:18,110 --> 00:08:20,240
I'll beat you using my mind.

181
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,100
(grumbling)

182
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,190
That's it!

183
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:26,130
(grunting)

184
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:29,150
Now die!

185
00:08:29,150 --> 00:08:31,020
(grunting)

186
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:34,050
He cheated, he just stabbed
the poor guy with a weapon!

187
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:35,130
Well, that's that.

188
00:08:35,130 --> 00:08:38,240
That guy got what he deserved
the way he was mouthin' off.

189
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,160
Using a suntetsu
was a dirty tactic,

190
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:43,060
but it's over.

191
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:48,200
(grunting)

192
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:51,170
(groaning)

193
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:55,020
♪

194
00:08:55,020 --> 00:08:58,090
You don't even have it
in you to fight fairly.

195
00:08:58,090 --> 00:09:00,050
I give up, I give up!

196
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:02,000
And yet I'm cheating as well.

197
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,090
If I were to use all my power,
there'd be nothing left of you.

198
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:08,070
So maybe it's best if
I just use one finger.

199
00:09:08,070 --> 00:09:13,270
♪

200
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:16,030
(groaning)

201
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:19,270
♪

202
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:23,160
(groaning and panting)

203
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:26,190
I hope in the future you'll
be a little more considerate.

204
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:28,210
How did he do that?

205
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:36,210
Up until now, you guys have
been getting away with a lot,

206
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:38,160
but if you're going
to use your sword,

207
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,060
then I will show you no mercy.

208
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:42,250
Democracy's a good idea,

209
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,230
but before you try to
correct our government,

210
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:46,230
why don't you correct yourself?

211
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:49,180
Now pay your bill and
leave here peacefully,

212
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:53,160
and don't let us see you again.

213
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:56,150
Kenshin, thanks a lot for
getting them to pay their bill.

214
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:58,010
They even left a tip!

215
00:09:58,010 --> 00:09:59,270
(groaning)

216
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:01,250
I'm glad everything
turned out well.

217
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:05,220
Now all of you can go back
to your peaceful lives.

218
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:07,120
I just can't stand bullies.

219
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,250
So, how's your head
feeling, swordsman?

220
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,040
Thanks for asking.

221
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:13,090
Except for a little bump,
I'll be all right.

222
00:10:13,090 --> 00:10:14,100
Glad to hear it.

223
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,260
You knew that bowl
was flying your way,

224
00:10:15,260 --> 00:10:18,160
but you chose not to move
and got that bump.

225
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,020
What?

226
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,140
I know you could
probably sense

227
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:23,190
that flying rice bowl was
gonna hit you in the head,

228
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:26,030
but you kept your head
right in the way.

229
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:27,090
You knew if you ducked,

230
00:10:27,090 --> 00:10:30,180
your lady friend would catch
that bowl right in the face.

231
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:32,140
Am I right?

232
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:34,250
You're giving me
way too much credit.

233
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:36,270
You're smart and humble.

234
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:40,160
I think I'd like to have a match
with you and really test you.

235
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,260
Thanks for the offer,
but no thanks.

236
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:46,000
Well, let me know if you
ever have an urge to fight.

237
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,060
I'm living in a shack
near the outskirts of town

238
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:49,210
if you want to find me.

239
00:10:49,210 --> 00:10:51,140
-See ya.
-Huh?

240
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:58,040
♪

241
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,140
Boy, he's odd.

242
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:01,050
From the way he acted,
I couldn't tell

243
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:03,090
if he was a good or bad person.

244
00:11:03,090 --> 00:11:05,080
All he cares about is fighting.

245
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,160
That's wrong.

246
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:10,250
He seems good,
but he's a little strange.

247
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:11,270
Wait a minute!

248
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,170
Oh, so you know him
from somewhere?

249
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:14,210
That's not it.

250
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:17,000
He left without paying his bill.

251
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:20,060
You mean he just ate and ran?

252
00:11:20,060 --> 00:11:21,280
So that's the new
fighter in town

253
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:23,090
that I've been hearing about?

254
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:24,140
(laughing)

255
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:28,170
I could use him to take care
of some unfinished business.

256
00:11:28,170 --> 00:11:30,050
(chuckling)

257
00:11:30,050 --> 00:11:31,060
Hmm.

258
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:37,000
(dog barking)

259
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,260
So you want me to take
care of this guy, huh?

260
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:44,040
Well, I'm not an assassin.

261
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:48,000
I think a man's living or
dying should be left to fate.

262
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:55,240
I just really enjoy
fighting, that's all.

263
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,120
(sighs)

264
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:00,020
Like I said,
getting money to kill a man

265
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,160
doesn't interest me.

266
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:04,060
But I guarantee you,
this job will provide you

267
00:12:04,060 --> 00:12:07,230
with a lot of fun.

268
00:12:07,230 --> 00:12:10,270
That Kenshin is very tough.

269
00:12:10,270 --> 00:12:12,150
Huh.

270
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:14,160
I think you must be
backing him in this fight

271
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:17,030
and stand to make
a lot of money if I lose.

272
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,180
Well, I'll give you a hot tip

273
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,200
that might save you
a lot of grief.

274
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:23,020
Don't bet against me, Gohei.

275
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:24,020
(laughing)

276
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:25,180
Who says that I'm betting?

277
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:27,210
So, you're not in
it for the money.

278
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:29,230
I just want to see
a royal battle.

279
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:31,250
I love a good fight.

280
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,190
I think a match between you
and Kenshin would be great.

281
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:36,280
And there's something
else that you should know.

282
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:39,230
It's Kenshin,
he has a secret.

283
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:41,190
He has another name,

284
00:12:41,190 --> 00:12:44,160
a name that I'm sure
you've heard of.

285
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:47,010
He's Battousai the Slasher.

286
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:49,060
Are you certain, Gohei?

287
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,230
Positive; here's your chance
to make yourself a name

288
00:12:51,230 --> 00:12:53,100
in the fighting world.

289
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,230
Listen, I'll give you
10,000 yen to fight him,

290
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,100
and when you win,
you'll be famous.

291
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:59,080
What could be better?

292
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:01,180
But I don't care
about fame or money.

293
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,150
Huh?

294
00:13:06,050 --> 00:13:09,220
What's important is that I and
my Zanza have a true challenge.

295
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:11,100
That's what matters.

296
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,200
Huh?

297
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:17,130
Thank you for this great
opportunity to fight Battousai.

298
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:19,210
So, the legendary Slasher
will have a chance

299
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:21,220
to meet my friend Zanza.

300
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:40,200
♪

301
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,290
Yes.

302
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:43,160
He's the perfect mercenary

303
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:46,180
to handle the task
of eliminating Kenshin.

304
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:49,180
(laughing)

305
00:13:49,180 --> 00:13:52,080
♪

306
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:54,190
Sanosuke and his Zanza,

307
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:56,190
a famous fighter
in his own right

308
00:13:56,190 --> 00:14:00,150
in the dark, shadowy world
of underworld combat.

309
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:02,080
Wherever this lone wolf travels,

310
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,170
he strikes terror in the
heart of his opponents,

311
00:14:04,170 --> 00:14:07,100
and now he's going to do me
a favor no one else can:

312
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:09,130
take Kenshin out of the picture.

313
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:12,070
The character painted on his
back couldn't be more true.

314
00:14:12,070 --> 00:14:15,040
He truly is bad.

315
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,130
I hope he makes Kenshin suffer

316
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:19,260
before he snuffs out his life.

317
00:14:19,260 --> 00:14:38,220
♪

318
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:41,240
Because of Kenshin,
I can no longer hold the sword

319
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,200
I dedicated my whole
life to mastering.

320
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:48,130
Watching him die will
be my sweet revenge.

321
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:55,160
(soft murmuring)

322
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,260
(snoring)

323
00:14:57,260 --> 00:15:01,160
(sipping)

324
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,498
(bell tolling)

325
00:15:02,498 --> 00:15:03,280
Huh?

326
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:05,010
It's one o'clock.

327
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:06,120
I must've dozed off.

328
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:09,000
I really must be
getting home now, Kenshin.

329
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,250
Dr. Gensai, why not spend
the rest of the night here?

330
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,260
Yumi and Suzie are sleeping
so soundly, don't leave!

331
00:15:14,260 --> 00:15:17,030
I'll let 'em sleep on
my mat if you want me to.

332
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:21,030
Well, you certainly can be
cooperative sometimes, Yoshi.

333
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:24,010
You know, you didn't have
to say "sometimes," Kori.

334
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:26,060
Hmm?

335
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:30,120
♪

336
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:32,120
There's someone at
your door, right now.

337
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:35,010
Huh?

338
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,180
At this time of night?

339
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:38,090
I didn't hear anyone.

340
00:15:38,090 --> 00:15:40,090
I didn't hear him,
but I could feel him.

341
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:42,000
Oh, oh.

342
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,280
It's someone who
follows his desires

343
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:46,040
no matter what
the consequences.

344
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,240
It's fighting man.

345
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:52,110
♪

346
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:53,230
You're right.

347
00:15:53,230 --> 00:15:55,120
I'm here to fight.

348
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,110
It's the guy we met at lunch.

349
00:15:57,110 --> 00:16:00,110
The guy with the
one-finger punch.

350
00:16:00,110 --> 00:16:02,040
I thought it might be you.

351
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,120
Did you understand me
when I explained earlier?

352
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,000
I don't want to fight you.

353
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,200
I cannot accept that decision.

354
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:12,080
Tonight, I have come here
to do battle with you,

355
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:15,180
and considering who you are,
I can accept nothing less.

356
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:18,010
So, you are
Battousai the Slasher,

357
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:20,050
a true Royalist
of the Restoration.

358
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:21,140
That's my reason.

359
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:23,130
(gasps)

360
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:27,220
What, how did he know that?

361
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:30,230
Nagasu sect Royalist
Battousai Himura.

362
00:16:30,230 --> 00:16:33,270
Your preferred technique is
the Hiten Mitsurugi style,

363
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:36,160
the Flying Sword
to Heaven philosophy.

364
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:39,190
You flatter me in how diligently
you've studied my career.

365
00:16:39,190 --> 00:16:42,170
Is that part of your
preparation to fight?

366
00:16:42,170 --> 00:16:45,280
Not really, it's just your
reputation is well-known.

367
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:48,190
But there's a lot of other
things about you I don't know.

368
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:50,070
For instance,
I heard of it,

369
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:51,130
but I have no idea

370
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:54,130
what your Hiten Mitsurugi
style looks like.

371
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:56,080
♪

372
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,120
I have other
questions to ask you.

373
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,250
What happened to change you
from a cold-hearted slasher

374
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:04,040
to a peaceful wanderer?

375
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:06,050
Since you won't
answer my questions,

376
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:07,210
I guess the only
way to find out

377
00:17:07,210 --> 00:17:10,280
is to fight you
and learn first-hand.

378
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,200
Hmm.

379
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:16,260
♪

380
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:18,200
(laughing)

381
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,210
♪

382
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:22,240
I don't know what
caused me to change.

383
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,020
Huh?

384
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:26,290
Maybe it was the insanity of
killing people that stopped me,

385
00:17:26,290 --> 00:17:28,290
or having so many people
wanting to fight me

386
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:30,100
to claim my title.

387
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:32,000
Allow me to ask you a question.

388
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,120
Why do you continue to
fight wherever you go?

389
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,030
You hate seeing the
powerless oppressed,

390
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:38,210
yet you insist on fighting
knowing you'll win.

391
00:17:38,210 --> 00:17:41,180
Well, you see, it's because...

392
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,280
It's no use.

393
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:45,030
It's better not to bring
up melancholy events

394
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:47,270
that happened in the
past before a fight.

395
00:17:47,270 --> 00:17:49,160
Like many others in your past,

396
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:52,000
I have come here to beat
you, legendary swordsman.

397
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:55,110
Battousai must be beaten,
and I will succeed him!

398
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:58,040
There is no more time for words!

399
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:01,130
(wind howling)

400
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:04,290
♪

401
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:10,080
You know, I don't believe
I've introduced myself to you.

402
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:14,020
I am Sanosuke Sagara,
and this is my weapon Zanza.

403
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:19,120
Oh, my gosh!

404
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:26,080
My sword is named
after where I'm from.

405
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,140
I'm from Zanbato.

406
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,150
Zanbato?

407
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,230
Where in the heck is that?

408
00:18:29,230 --> 00:18:31,260
It's in the north,
a huge sword was built there

409
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:33,230
and it's designed to
cut an enemy horseman

410
00:18:33,230 --> 00:18:35,010
and his horse in two.

411
00:18:35,010 --> 00:18:37,270
The only problem is no one
has ever been strong enough

412
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,230
to use it effectively.

413
00:18:39,230 --> 00:18:41,200
(wind howling)

414
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:45,120
(wind stops)

415
00:18:46,210 --> 00:18:47,290
(laughing)

416
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:49,220
So now finally
the time has come

417
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:54,190
for there to be an answer to all
of our questions, Battousai.

418
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:57,060
(shouting)

419
00:18:57,060 --> 00:18:58,280
Kenshin, don't just stand there.

420
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,200
Take action.

421
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:03,170
(grunting)

422
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:14,160
♪

423
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,180
(gasps)

424
00:19:15,180 --> 00:19:18,070
♪

425
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:19,270
That was a very good
counter move,

426
00:19:19,270 --> 00:19:21,220
but it's not over yet.

427
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:23,220
Now take your sword out.

428
00:19:23,220 --> 00:19:25,060
Do it!

429
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:28,030
♪

430
00:19:28,030 --> 00:19:30,230
(gasps)

431
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,120
(grunting)

432
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,240
Hmm.

433
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:45,280
♪

434
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:47,030
Kenshin.

435
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:48,160
-Kenshin.
-It's Yumi.

436
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:50,190
Where are you?

437
00:19:50,190 --> 00:19:51,260
Kenshin?

438
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:53,090
Are you outside?

439
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:55,290
You both need to stay inside!

440
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,120
Women and children
should never witness

441
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:05,000
the savage reality of two men
fighting for their lives.

442
00:20:06,220 --> 00:20:08,270
Sanosuke, do you feel it?

443
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:12,070
Someone with a bloodthirsty
heart is watching us.

444
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:13,140
Really?

445
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,280
Huh?

446
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:16,030
Uh-oh.

447
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:20,090
(groaning)

448
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:21,150
What was that?

449
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:23,130
Really ferocious termites.

450
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:25,140
Well, you've
dodged me this time.

451
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:28,160
But you can rest assured
there'll be another time.

452
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,220
Once I get
an opponent in my sights,

453
00:20:30,220 --> 00:20:32,030
it's just a matter of time

454
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:34,230
until that adversary
is defeated.

455
00:20:34,230 --> 00:20:36,130
Until next time.

456
00:20:36,130 --> 00:20:37,220
(departing footsteps)

457
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:39,010
Until next time.

458
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:40,050
What's his motive?

459
00:20:40,050 --> 00:20:42,230
Why does he hate samurai
so much he must kill them?

460
00:20:42,230 --> 00:20:49,100
♪

461
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,160
It doesn't look like he's
going to let me walk away

462
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,210
from this fight
no matter what I do.

463
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:54,270
It's all right.

464
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:56,100
I'm glad you're all right.

465
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:57,210
(giggling)

466
00:20:57,210 --> 00:20:59,020
What was that about?

467
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:01,100
Hey, I've got news
for both of you.

468
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:04,070
Come on, Yoshi and I will
carry you two piggyback

469
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:05,210
all the way home.

470
00:21:05,210 --> 00:21:08,270
(cheering and giggling)

471
00:21:08,270 --> 00:21:19,240
♪

472
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:22,260
That was our first
encounter with Sanosuke,

473
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:26,130
but it was just the beginning
of the adventure we would share.

474
00:21:26,130 --> 00:21:31,270
♪

475
00:21:34,220 --> 00:21:46,230
♪

476
00:21:46,230 --> 00:21:48,230
(singing in foreign language)

477
00:21:48,230 --> 00:23:13,090
♪

